1
00:00:08,600 --> 00:00:10,961
♪Love's little quiz
takes seven parts sweet♪

2
00:00:10,962 --> 00:00:13,559
♪And three parts bitter,
till you and I meet♪

3
00:00:13,560 --> 00:00:17,159
♪I pretend I'm not there,
but secretly stay♪

4
00:00:17,160 --> 00:00:26,399
♪Waiting for you♪

5
00:00:26,400 --> 00:00:31,400
♪We've got so many
romantic dreams to unfold♪

6
00:00:31,480 --> 00:00:36,224
♪Finally hearing
the I love you I long to hold♪

7
00:00:36,225 --> 00:00:39,839
♪Falling fast
into the swirl of your eyes♪

8
00:00:39,840 --> 00:00:42,399
♪It's just too tempting, so tempting♪

9
00:00:42,400 --> 00:00:45,499
♪Never could I have guessed♪

10
00:00:45,500 --> 00:00:46,499
♪My heart's rhythm♪

11
00:00:46,500 --> 00:00:49,632
♪How beautiful it is, meeting you♪

12
00:01:02,975 --> 00:01:05,961
=Late to Love=
(Adapted from "My Husband Is A Billionaire!")

13
00:01:05,962 --> 00:01:08,760
=Episode 8=

14
00:01:11,859 --> 00:01:12,939
Huo Beiyan,

15
00:01:13,499 --> 00:01:16,459
yesterday you said you didn't like me.

16
00:01:16,580 --> 00:01:19,539
But now you keep bringing me food
every single day.

17
00:01:19,580 --> 00:01:20,939
Do you...

18
00:01:24,139 --> 00:01:25,379
It's like this.

19
00:01:25,380 --> 00:01:26,980
Because

20
00:01:27,419 --> 00:01:29,418
there are a lot of people watching us.

21
00:01:29,419 --> 00:01:31,299
We have to sell the act completely.

22
00:01:31,300 --> 00:01:32,338
Otherwise,

23
00:01:32,339 --> 00:01:33,860
everything we've done so far

24
00:01:34,020 --> 00:01:35,459
could fall apart.

25
00:01:38,059 --> 00:01:39,218
But let me be clear.

26
00:01:39,219 --> 00:01:40,539
I'm extremely busy.

27
00:01:40,540 --> 00:01:42,539
I can't exactly help you provide

28
00:01:42,540 --> 00:01:44,099
all that emotional value stuff.

29
00:01:44,100 --> 00:01:45,819
Do you feel like you're losing out?

30
00:01:45,820 --> 00:01:47,618
I never asked you to provide it.

31
00:01:47,619 --> 00:01:48,860
Just focus

32
00:01:49,139 --> 00:01:51,498
on playing the role of Mrs. Huo properly.

33
00:01:51,499 --> 00:01:52,099
Fine.

34
00:01:52,100 --> 00:01:53,459
You said it yourself.

35
00:01:53,660 --> 00:01:54,539
Eat.

36
00:01:56,487 --> 00:01:58,207
(Li Wanru)

37
00:02:00,925 --> 00:02:02,320
(Li Wanru)

38
00:02:03,660 --> 00:02:04,579
Ugh.

39
00:02:04,900 --> 00:02:05,900
What now?

40
00:02:06,699 --> 00:02:08,040
My stepmother, obviously.

41
00:02:08,040 --> 00:02:10,200
Ever since she found out I married
into the Huo family,

42
00:02:10,200 --> 00:02:11,338
she's been clinging to me

43
00:02:11,339 --> 00:02:12,539
like a fly that won't go away.

44
00:02:13,740 --> 00:02:14,538
I'm telling you now.

45
00:02:14,539 --> 00:02:17,338
If she brings Xu Yin to bother you later,
do not engage with them.

46
00:02:17,339 --> 00:02:19,139
Relax. I'm not that free.

47
00:02:25,900 --> 00:02:26,780
Yes?

48
00:02:26,900 --> 00:02:28,299
Nange, sweetheart,

49
00:02:28,300 --> 00:02:29,618
it's me, Mom.

50
00:02:29,619 --> 00:02:30,739
Are you busy?

51
00:02:30,740 --> 00:02:31,620
Yes.

52
00:02:32,219 --> 00:02:33,818
Nothing important, really.

53
00:02:33,819 --> 00:02:34,778
I just wanted to ask.

54
00:02:34,779 --> 00:02:35,498
You see,

55
00:02:35,499 --> 00:02:36,498
now that you're married,

56
00:02:36,499 --> 00:02:37,618
when are you bringing

57
00:02:37,619 --> 00:02:40,419
Mr. Huo back to the Xu family
for a meal?

58
00:02:42,839 --> 00:02:44,778
Who was it again that threw me
out of the Xu family?

59
00:02:44,779 --> 00:02:46,419
I'm never going back there again.

60
00:02:47,460 --> 00:02:50,058
Let bygones be bygones.

61
00:02:50,059 --> 00:02:52,498
Now that you're married,
you should still come back for a visit.

62
00:02:52,499 --> 00:02:53,778
It's basic etiquette.

63
00:02:53,779 --> 00:02:55,899
Don't think I don't know
what you're really after.

64
00:02:55,900 --> 00:02:58,060
I'm telling you right now, impossible.

65
00:03:01,260 --> 00:03:01,920
Well, look at that.

66
00:03:01,920 --> 00:03:04,280
Now that she's climbed the social ladder,
she thinks she's untouchable.

67
00:03:04,819 --> 00:03:05,899
Don't say that.

68
00:03:05,900 --> 00:03:07,058
I refuse to believe

69
00:03:07,059 --> 00:03:09,220
there's no way into the Huo family.

70
00:03:09,580 --> 00:03:10,938
Come on, Mom.

71
00:03:10,939 --> 00:03:12,618
Even I can see through your tactics.

72
00:03:12,619 --> 00:03:14,259
You only know how to play easy wins.

73
00:03:14,860 --> 00:03:16,139
What would you know?

74
00:03:17,099 --> 00:03:19,740
Right now, I'm waiting
for the perfect opportunity.

75
00:03:21,420 --> 00:03:22,939
Who is it?

76
00:03:30,339 --> 00:03:31,299
You are…?

77
00:03:31,300 --> 00:03:33,340
You must be Auntie Li Wanru.

78
00:03:33,580 --> 00:03:34,098
That's right.

79
00:03:34,099 --> 00:03:35,259
I'm Huo Beiyan's cousin.

80
00:03:35,260 --> 00:03:36,419
My name is Huo Zichen.

81
00:03:38,659 --> 00:03:39,859
Mr. Zichen?

82
00:03:39,860 --> 00:03:41,699
Quick, come inside.

83
00:03:44,260 --> 00:03:45,979
Look who's here.

84
00:03:48,339 --> 00:03:49,378
Mr. Zichen,

85
00:03:49,379 --> 00:03:51,579
this is my other daughter, Xu Yin.

86
00:03:51,580 --> 00:03:53,058
Ever since Nange got married,

87
00:03:53,059 --> 00:03:55,859
she's the only one still single
staying by my side.

88
00:03:56,260 --> 00:03:57,259
Hello.

89
00:03:57,260 --> 00:03:58,379
Hello.

90
00:03:59,260 --> 00:04:00,139
Auntie,

91
00:04:00,580 --> 00:04:02,500
you can just call me Zichen from now on.

92
00:04:02,779 --> 00:04:05,179
I picked up this gift on the way over.

93
00:04:05,180 --> 00:04:07,360
My cousin's been very busy lately,
so as the younger one,

94
00:04:07,360 --> 00:04:08,780
I thought I should come visit instead.

95
00:04:08,819 --> 00:04:09,618
Zichen,

96
00:04:09,619 --> 00:04:11,338
you're too thoughtful.

97
00:04:11,339 --> 00:04:12,819
Please sit down.

98
00:04:13,020 --> 00:04:14,098
Please sit down.

99
00:04:14,099 --> 00:04:15,180
Come, have a seat.

100
00:04:15,740 --> 00:04:16,899
Really.

101
00:04:16,900 --> 00:04:18,619
You didn't have to bring gifts.

102
00:04:19,140 --> 00:04:20,680
I just got back from overseas,

103
00:04:20,680 --> 00:04:23,098
and the first thing I heard was
that my brother got married.

104
00:04:23,099 --> 00:04:24,340
Honestly, I was shocked.

105
00:04:25,060 --> 00:04:26,460
Tell me about it.

106
00:04:26,500 --> 00:04:29,098
Nange's always been independent
since she was little.

107
00:04:29,099 --> 00:04:30,459
Even we only found out

108
00:04:30,460 --> 00:04:33,179
about the marriage two days
before they registered.

109
00:04:33,539 --> 00:04:34,900
Right, Yin?

110
00:04:37,339 --> 00:04:38,499
Yeah.

111
00:04:38,779 --> 00:04:41,619
I guess when fate arrives,

112
00:04:41,620 --> 00:04:43,460
there's just no stopping it.

113
00:04:45,099 --> 00:04:47,580
Fate really is mysterious sometimes.

114
00:04:48,539 --> 00:04:51,658
But my brother's personality
has always been pretty cold and distant.

115
00:04:51,659 --> 00:04:53,459
For him to care this much
about his wife,

116
00:04:53,460 --> 00:04:54,579
she must have something

117
00:04:54,580 --> 00:04:56,539
truly special about her.

118
00:04:56,739 --> 00:04:58,179
Of course she does.

119
00:04:58,820 --> 00:04:59,979
Exactly.

120
00:05:01,140 --> 00:05:02,059
Oh right.

121
00:05:02,060 --> 00:05:03,820
I heard someone mention

122
00:05:03,900 --> 00:05:05,338
that her doctoral thesis

123
00:05:05,339 --> 00:05:07,139
is extremely difficult this time.

124
00:05:07,140 --> 00:05:08,418
My cousin even bought out

125
00:05:08,419 --> 00:05:09,739
an entire lab at Linhai for her.

126
00:05:09,779 --> 00:05:11,699
She never really tells us much

127
00:05:11,700 --> 00:05:12,920
about her research anyway.

128
00:05:12,920 --> 00:05:14,479
My mom and I
can't understand a word of it.

129
00:05:14,479 --> 00:05:16,099
She acts mysterious all day long.

130
00:05:16,339 --> 00:05:17,380
Yin.

131
00:05:19,539 --> 00:05:20,819
I-I didn't mean

132
00:05:20,820 --> 00:05:22,619
that in a bad way.

133
00:05:22,620 --> 00:05:23,820
No, it's fine.

134
00:05:24,099 --> 00:05:25,400
You two are sisters after all.

135
00:05:25,400 --> 00:05:27,160
My brother and I
are like that all the time too.

136
00:05:27,659 --> 00:05:29,059
Right.

137
00:05:30,620 --> 00:05:32,459
Yin, stop sitting there.

138
00:05:32,460 --> 00:05:34,179
Pour Zichen some water.

139
00:05:34,900 --> 00:05:35,820
Okay.

140
00:05:36,539 --> 00:05:38,620
(A research topic ordinary people
can't even understand)

141
00:05:38,620 --> 00:05:40,340
(and she still insists
on being so secretive?)

142
00:05:40,500 --> 00:05:41,900
(Xu Nange,)

143
00:05:42,260 --> 00:05:44,499
(I'm getting more and more curious.)

144
00:05:45,620 --> 00:05:46,899
So the final conclusion is,

145
00:05:46,900 --> 00:05:48,619
after verification
by a third-party laboratory,

146
00:05:48,620 --> 00:05:51,459
all of Dr. X's experimental data
can be successfully reproduced.

147
00:05:51,460 --> 00:05:53,019
There's no possibility of fabrication.

148
00:05:53,020 --> 00:05:55,680
By the way, Mr. Huo, I also had someone
look into Dr. X's background.

149
00:05:55,680 --> 00:05:58,520
Although this person
is extremely mysterious,

150
00:05:58,520 --> 00:06:01,019
their reputation in academic circles
is impeccable.

151
00:06:01,020 --> 00:06:01,499
Oh right,

152
00:06:01,500 --> 00:06:03,020
this is the investigation report.

153
00:06:06,620 --> 00:06:07,819
Same as before,

154
00:06:07,820 --> 00:06:09,020
find them as soon as possible.

155
00:06:09,739 --> 00:06:10,459
Don't worry.

156
00:06:10,460 --> 00:06:11,619
Leave it to me.

157
00:06:13,460 --> 00:06:15,139
Mr. Huo, look.

158
00:06:15,140 --> 00:06:16,858
I understand you invested

159
00:06:16,859 --> 00:06:19,099
in a private laboratory for Madam's sake.

160
00:06:20,460 --> 00:06:21,658
But did you really need

161
00:06:21,659 --> 00:06:22,899
to rent out

162
00:06:22,900 --> 00:06:24,098
the entire building

163
00:06:24,099 --> 00:06:25,659
next to the lab too?

164
00:06:27,009 --> 00:06:28,800
It's not like she can use
that much space anyway.

165
00:06:31,779 --> 00:06:33,099
Is there a problem?

166
00:06:34,140 --> 00:06:35,499
No problem at all.

167
00:06:38,060 --> 00:06:38,858
Mr. Huo is getting

168
00:06:38,859 --> 00:06:40,338
more lovestruck by the day.

169
00:06:40,339 --> 00:06:42,380
Less nonsense. Go make the arrangements.

170
00:06:42,739 --> 00:06:44,260
Right away.

171
00:06:56,539 --> 00:06:58,019
(I'll pick you up later.)

172
00:06:58,020 --> 00:06:59,739
(Family dinner tonight.)

173
00:07:02,299 --> 00:07:03,059
Beiyan,

174
00:07:03,060 --> 00:07:05,699
how's the company's
medical-industry transition going?

175
00:07:05,700 --> 00:07:07,579
I've already collected
the board's opinions.

176
00:07:07,580 --> 00:07:08,978
More than half of them

177
00:07:08,979 --> 00:07:10,139
oppose the transition.

178
00:07:10,140 --> 00:07:11,780
So what are you planning to do?

179
00:07:12,020 --> 00:07:13,260
I think

180
00:07:13,900 --> 00:07:15,538
the only way to convince everyone

181
00:07:15,539 --> 00:07:17,538
is with an absolutely authoritative

182
00:07:17,539 --> 00:07:19,340
transition plan.

183
00:07:19,900 --> 00:07:20,619
That's why

184
00:07:20,620 --> 00:07:21,699
I've decided to work with

185
00:07:21,700 --> 00:07:23,259
Dr. X,

186
00:07:23,260 --> 00:07:24,700
the expert in neuroscience.

187
00:07:26,700 --> 00:07:28,340
What's wrong? Are you okay?

188
00:07:29,299 --> 00:07:30,418
I'm fine.

189
00:07:30,419 --> 00:07:31,699
I'm fine, really.

190
00:07:31,700 --> 00:07:33,499
Go on, continue.

191
00:07:35,859 --> 00:07:36,899
Dr. X?

192
00:07:36,900 --> 00:07:38,579
We don't even know who this person is.

193
00:07:38,580 --> 00:07:40,859
Wouldn't partnering
with them be too risky?

194
00:07:41,299 --> 00:07:42,059
Dad,

195
00:07:42,060 --> 00:07:43,098
they may be

196
00:07:43,099 --> 00:07:45,299
Grandma's only hope.

197
00:07:49,299 --> 00:07:52,179
Normally speaking,

198
00:07:52,500 --> 00:07:54,459
an expert at that level

199
00:07:54,460 --> 00:07:56,539
wouldn't need to hide their identity.

200
00:07:56,739 --> 00:07:59,340
If they refuse to show themselves,

201
00:07:59,859 --> 00:08:01,859
could they actually be a fraud?

202
00:08:05,179 --> 00:08:06,259
I just think

203
00:08:06,260 --> 00:08:07,778
what you're discussing

204
00:08:07,779 --> 00:08:08,939
sounds very important.

205
00:08:08,940 --> 00:08:11,699
So everyone should probably

206
00:08:11,700 --> 00:08:13,220
be more cautious.

207
00:08:14,219 --> 00:08:16,580
Nange makes a good point too.

208
00:08:17,340 --> 00:08:19,180
But I already had someone
run a background check.

209
00:08:19,180 --> 00:08:20,778
Dr. X's research results

210
00:08:20,779 --> 00:08:22,019
all hold up under scrutiny.

211
00:08:22,020 --> 00:08:23,739
And their reputation is excellent.

212
00:08:25,179 --> 00:08:26,220
How about this?

213
00:08:26,419 --> 00:08:27,259
Nange,

214
00:08:27,260 --> 00:08:28,619
you're also a medical PhD.

215
00:08:28,620 --> 00:08:31,019
Once I find Dr. X,
I'll arrange a meeting between you two.

216
00:08:31,020 --> 00:08:32,840
You can evaluate
their professional level yourself,

217
00:08:32,840 --> 00:08:34,560
then we'll decide whether
to cooperate with them.

218
00:08:36,100 --> 00:08:37,300
Sure.

219
00:08:40,140 --> 00:08:41,339
You all continue talking.

220
00:08:41,340 --> 00:08:43,220
I'll go upstairs
and check on Grandma first.

221
00:08:43,380 --> 00:08:45,779
Alright.
Our Nange has worked hard for this.

222
00:08:48,939 --> 00:08:51,859
You're going to help me

223
00:08:52,260 --> 00:08:54,700
find the best doctor?

224
00:08:56,419 --> 00:08:57,899
Grandma, don't worry.

225
00:08:58,220 --> 00:08:59,339
I'm actually the Dr. X

226
00:08:59,340 --> 00:09:01,379
Huo Beiyan has been searching
for all along.

227
00:09:01,620 --> 00:09:04,060
I'll definitely do everything I can
to cure you.

228
00:09:04,740 --> 00:09:06,540
But right now, I'm thinking...

229
00:09:06,779 --> 00:09:09,019
How can I keep my identity hidden?

230
00:09:09,020 --> 00:09:12,060
Why do you need to hide?

231
00:09:13,140 --> 00:09:14,499
Because,

232
00:09:16,220 --> 00:09:18,460
I have a secret that can't be told.

233
00:09:19,475 --> 00:09:23,832
(One year earlier)

234
00:09:25,340 --> 00:09:26,859
My name is Xu Nange.

235
00:09:27,380 --> 00:09:29,739
Today is December 17th, 2025,

236
00:09:29,740 --> 00:09:31,219
8:52 in the morning.

237
00:09:31,220 --> 00:09:32,578
Starting today,

238
00:09:32,579 --> 00:09:34,979
I will begin efficacy testing

239
00:09:34,980 --> 00:09:37,058
on the so-called
Alzheimer's miracle drug, NIT-33.

240
00:09:37,059 --> 00:09:38,619
Based on my prior investigation,

241
00:09:38,620 --> 00:09:40,499
this drug is clearly harmful
to the human body.

242
00:09:40,500 --> 00:09:42,698
Yet NIT-33 has already become
a massive overseas bestseller,

243
00:09:42,699 --> 00:09:43,739
earning billions in profit.

244
00:09:43,740 --> 00:09:45,259
So starting today,

245
00:09:45,260 --> 00:09:47,219
I intend to expose this enormous lie.

246
00:09:47,220 --> 00:09:48,778
And to achieve that goal,

247
00:09:48,779 --> 00:09:49,458
my life

248
00:09:49,459 --> 00:09:51,458
may be placed in considerable danger.

249
00:09:51,459 --> 00:09:53,538
My experimental data
and research materials

250
00:09:53,539 --> 00:09:55,298
require the highest level
of security clearance.

251
00:09:55,299 --> 00:09:57,178
Without my biometric authentication,

252
00:09:57,179 --> 00:10:00,420
(Clause 2: Data Security)
no one is allowed to touch anything.

253
00:10:00,500 --> 00:10:01,619
That includes you.

254
00:10:01,800 --> 00:10:03,099
I can't finish my thesis anymore.

255
00:10:03,100 --> 00:10:04,219
I don't need money.

256
00:10:04,220 --> 00:10:06,979
I want the entire laboratory
at Linhai Medical School.

257
00:10:07,020 --> 00:10:07,979
So,

258
00:10:07,980 --> 00:10:11,099
I'll use my doctoral studies
as a cover for my real identity.

259
00:10:11,100 --> 00:10:12,660
Under the anonymous name "X",

260
00:10:12,699 --> 00:10:14,650
I'll publicly release the progress
of my experiments.

261
00:10:14,650 --> 00:10:17,200
This matter is too important.
I'm recording this video as evidence.

262
00:10:17,200 --> 00:10:18,499
If anything happens to me,

263
00:10:18,500 --> 00:10:20,300
rule out the possibility
of suicide entirely.

264
00:10:24,659 --> 00:10:25,739
Mrs. Huo,

265
00:10:25,740 --> 00:10:27,420
Madam Li Wanru has arrived.

266
00:10:27,699 --> 00:10:28,658
What is she doing here?

267
00:10:28,659 --> 00:10:30,139
She's here for the family dinner.

268
00:10:30,140 --> 00:10:32,379
It seems Mr. Zichen invited her.

269
00:10:32,380 --> 00:10:33,619
(Huo Zichen?)

270
00:10:33,620 --> 00:10:34,779
Understood.

271
00:10:35,980 --> 00:10:37,619
Grandma, I'll be right back, okay?

272
00:10:43,299 --> 00:10:44,660
Is this for me?

273
00:10:48,299 --> 00:10:48,979
Okay.

274
00:10:48,980 --> 00:10:50,220
Thank you, Grandma.

275
00:10:52,419 --> 00:10:53,820
I'll be back soon.

276
00:11:07,819 --> 00:11:09,180
What are you doing here?

277
00:11:10,539 --> 00:11:11,658
Nange,

278
00:11:11,659 --> 00:11:13,458
you're Mrs. Huo now.

279
00:11:13,459 --> 00:11:15,538
Of course we had to come visit.

280
00:11:15,539 --> 00:11:16,499
With the Huo family

281
00:11:16,500 --> 00:11:18,058
supporting us,

282
00:11:18,059 --> 00:11:20,019
the Xu family's future
will definitely soar.

283
00:11:20,459 --> 00:11:21,778
Whether I'm Mrs. Huo or not

284
00:11:21,779 --> 00:11:23,379
has nothing to do with the Xu family.

285
00:11:24,020 --> 00:11:25,219
Watch your tone.

286
00:11:25,220 --> 00:11:26,899
Weren't you raised by the Xu family?

287
00:11:26,980 --> 00:11:28,538
Just say a word to Huo Beiyan.

288
00:11:28,539 --> 00:11:30,698
Do you know how hard it is
to secure projects these days?

289
00:11:30,699 --> 00:11:32,339
If any suitable projects come up,

290
00:11:32,340 --> 00:11:33,859
just let the Xu family handle them.

291
00:11:35,340 --> 00:11:37,458
The Huo family has its own standards
for partnerships.

292
00:11:37,459 --> 00:11:39,899
I won't interfere,
and I don't have that authority anyway.

293
00:11:40,299 --> 00:11:41,658
The Huo family's standards?

294
00:11:41,659 --> 00:11:43,940
Wouldn't Huo Beiyan
be the one setting them?

295
00:11:44,299 --> 00:11:45,219
Besides,

296
00:11:45,220 --> 00:11:47,060
doesn't he have another cousin?

297
00:11:50,980 --> 00:11:52,099
Li Wanru,

298
00:11:52,699 --> 00:11:53,940
I'm warning you.

299
00:11:54,059 --> 00:11:56,019
Stay away from Huo Zichen.

300
00:11:59,579 --> 00:12:01,660
Our dear in-laws have arrived.

301
00:12:02,300 --> 00:12:03,859
Forgive me
for not welcoming you properly.

302
00:12:03,860 --> 00:12:05,058
This must be our in-law,

303
00:12:05,059 --> 00:12:06,540
Old Mr. Huo himself!

304
00:12:30,662 --> 00:12:34,436
♪What destiny brought us to meet♪

305
00:12:34,437 --> 00:12:37,757
♪Two different worlds, a love so sweet♪

306
00:12:37,762 --> 00:12:41,136
♪A wish we made
in a past life, it seems♪

307
00:12:41,137 --> 00:12:43,991
♪Destined to cross time and dream ♪

308
00:12:43,992 --> 00:12:47,832
♪Like a fairytale story told♪

309
00:12:47,912 --> 00:12:51,169
♪A gentle breeze feels so bold♪

310
00:12:51,187 --> 00:12:54,873
♪As your hair brushes past your ear♪

311
00:12:54,874 --> 00:12:57,231
♪I long to kiss your cheek, my dear♪

312
00:12:57,232 --> 00:13:01,471
♪All my longing, all my love for you♪

313
00:13:01,472 --> 00:13:04,032
♪Has never changed, it's forever true♪

314
00:13:04,474 --> 00:13:10,872
♪It's the hand of fate
that we meet again♪

315
00:13:11,674 --> 00:13:16,112
♪Let me hold you once again♪

316
00:13:16,362 --> 00:13:19,282
♪Resting against your chest♪

317
00:13:19,632 --> 00:13:24,873
♪Your warmth shines like stars at night♪

318
00:13:24,874 --> 00:13:29,673
♪Let me kiss you once again♪

319
00:13:29,674 --> 00:13:32,473
♪No reason needed♪

320
00:13:32,474 --> 00:13:34,671
♪My heart belongs to you♪

321
00:13:34,672 --> 00:13:40,392
♪I'm not afraid
to cross time to find you♪

